Widget Properties for Analytics Dashboard

Use text widgets to emphasize important data, make your dashboards more scannable, and tell a more compelling data story.

Drag a text widget onto your dashboard.
Type in the text box.
Select and format text.
Use standard and custom colors, adjust character size, and apply formatting to words and individual characters.
To format text that’s based on query data, first select and add the query field.

Keep these considerations in mind when using enhanced text formatting.

When creating a binding using a text widget, text widget controls are unavailable. Additional changes to text and text formatting must be done using JSON.
Conditional formatting colors take precedence over colors applied using a text widget.
Apply formatting to the entire portion of query-based text.

The text widget doesn’t support multiple selections from a filter widget.
By default the text widget uses the first value when multiple values are selected from the filter widget.
title: Enhancing Data Visualization with Text Widgets
